=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Overviews_Operators_ex48 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 1002 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and sustained envelope, energy distribution is late, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: sustained
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: stable
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: late

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 1002.1316
  harmonic_decay_rate: -7.7472
  harmonic_regularity: 0.1541
  pitch_clarity: 318.8034
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -3.5598
  resonance_freq: 990.5273

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Operators Example 48
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Overviews/Operators.html
// Tags: Operators, Overviews
// ---
// --- Example 48 ---
(
{
    var a;
    a = Line.ar(-2, 2, 0.01);
    a.clip2
}.plot
)

{ FSinOsc.ar(400).clip2(0.2) }.play; // clipping distortion

{ FSinOsc.ar(1000).clip2(Line.kr(0,1,8)) }.play;
